HEADWORD: Conventionality
<hw>Con*ven`tion*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Conventionalities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<def>The state of being conventional; adherence to social formalities or
usages; that which is established by conventional use; one of the
customary usages of social life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conventionalization</ent>⟦br⟧
